  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 56 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1190 mg
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hot-n-hearty-chicken-pizzas-5a99c7c9ae08b575c96a3012
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Place rack in position closest to flame and heat broiler to high. Pat @chicken breast strips{20%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Heat @olive oil{4%tsp} in a large pan. Add chicken and season with @Italian seasoning{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, tossing occasionally, until cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, slice @zucchini{2} into thin rounds. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallots{2}. Toss zucchini and shallot with @olive oil{4%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} and spread out on a #baking sheet{}. Broil veggies on rack closest to flame until lightly browned, about ~{4%minutes}.

While veggies broil, mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Once veggies are done broiling, remove from sheet and transfer to a #plate{}. Place @flatbreads{4} on same sheet, then spread a thin layer of @crushed tomatoes{27.52%ounce} over top (we used half the container; if you like your pizza saucy, use more). Scatter garlic (to taste) over top.

Cut @fresh mozzarella{8%ounce} in half, then thinly slice. Scatter veggies from plate in an even layer over flatbreads, followed by chicken and @chili flakes{2%tsp} (to taste—start with ¼ tsp and add more if you like it hot). Spread out mozzarella slices in an even layer on top.

Place flatbreads under broiler and broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Transfer flatbreads to a #cutting board{} and cut into squares. Season with @salt{} and serve.

> TIP: If you have any chili flakes left over, serve them on the side as a garnish.